==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wem
<hw>Wem</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Womb</er>.]</ety>
<def>The abdomen; the uterus; the womb.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wem</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wem
<hw>Wem</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>wam</ets>,
<ets>wamm</ets>.]</ety> <def>Spot; blemish; harm; hurt.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wyclif.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Withouten <qex>wem</qex> of you, through foul and fair.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wem</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wem
<hw>Wem</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>wemman</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To stain; to blemish; to harm; to corrupt.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wemless</ent>⟦br⟧
